Package neureka.calculus.backend

Class ExecutionCall<DeviceType extends Device>

  • java.lang.Object
    • neureka.calculus.backend.ExecutionCall<DeviceType>
  • Type Parameters:
    DeviceType - The Device implementation targeted by an instance of this ExecutionCall!
    public class ExecutionCall<DeviceType extends Device>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a simple container holding relevant arguments needed to execute on a targeted Device which is specified by the type parameter below. It also holds a context map responsible for storing operation specific variables.

      • getDerivativeIndex

        public int getDerivativeIndex()
        This method returns an import property whose role might not be clear at first : An operation can have multiple inputs, however when calculating the derivative for a forward or backward pass then one must know which derivative ought to be calculated. So the "derivative index" targets said input. This property is -1 when no derivative should be calculated, however 0... when targeting an input to calculate the derivative of.
        Returns:
        The index of the input whose derivative ought to be calculated.
